      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The norm is that ethnic tensions are ever-present, and violence is a constant threat. In most areas, it's not a matter of if, but when, clashes will occur. The country is essentially fragmented into separate ethnic enclaves, with little to no interaction between groups. The capital city, Kinshasa, is a rare exception, but even there, tensions simmer just below the surface. In rural areas, militias and armed groups often control entire regions, making it difficult for people from different groups to live together peacefully.",
      "source": "target",
